Change token syntax in searches to {{field}}

This is to prevent collisions with bash variables which causes problems
for users not familiar with bash syntax and escaping. Should also be
easy to remember the syntax which is similar to jinja2.

The token names must match `[@#._]?[\w.-]+` to be detected.

Add new command urlsearch

`urlsearch` creates a hc search command from a Humio search url and
optionally executes the command afterwards.

`search` now outputs URLs to the Humio equivalent search to
seamlessly switch between the CLI and Humio.
